OL,3,CGo-ahead given to clean-up dumped
OL,4,Cwaste at Hoad's Wood ancient woodland
OL,6,FThe site was illegally felled in 2020,
OL,7,Fand then in July 2023 residents
OL,8,Freported lorries dumping truckloads of
OL,9,Fwaste at the Bluebell woodland.
OL,11,FThe activity finally stopped in
OL,12,FJanuary 2024 when the Environment
OL,13,FAgency blocked off the site and
OL,14,Fimposed an enforcement order
OL,15,Fpreventing access.
OL,17,FSince then, campaigners have been
OL,18,Fcalling for a clean-up of the area,
OL,19,Fwhich is estimated to cover around
OL,20,Ffour acres of land and stands up to
OL,21,F25ft high in places.
