OL,3,CGo-ahead given to clean-up dumped
OL,4,Cwaste at Hoad's Wood ancient woodland
OL,6,FCampaigners from the Rescue Hoad's
OL,7,FWood group, say that contractors have
OL,8,Fquoted the clean-up operation will
OL,9,Fcost #10m and today they welcomed the
OL,10,Fnews that emergency funds had been
OL,11,Fsecured to allow the clean-up to take
OL,12,Fplace.
OL,14,FA spokesman for the Rescue Hoad's Wood
OL,15,Fcampaign said: "We are thrilled to
OL,16,Fhear that the funding required to
OL,17,Fclear the 30,000 tonnes of illegally
OL,18,Fdumped landfill waste from Hoad's Wood
OL,19,Fis now approved.
